# Laravel Backend Standards

- Use Form Requests for validation; keep controllers thin.
- Place business logic in services/actions, not controllers.
- Use Policies/Gates for resource authorization (especially PDF downloads).
- Return consistent API/web responses and explicit error handling.
- Use Eloquent scopes/repositories only when they reduce duplication.
- Prefer queued jobs for heavy processing (imports, notifications, reports).
- Add feature tests for auth boundaries and download permissions.
- Use migrations with safe roll-forward/rollback strategy.
- Avoid N+1 queries; eager load intentionally and profile hot paths.
- Protect sensitive fields with proper casting, hidden attributes, and encryption when needed.
